9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 509, L.D. 802, “Resolve, Directing the
10 Department of Health and Human Services to Design a Mentoring Program for Youth Who
11 Have Extended Care and Support Agreements with the Department”
12 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 1. Department of Health and Human Services contract for mentoring
14 program. Resolved: That the Department of Health and Human Services shall amend
15 its contract CFS-25-627 with the Youth Leadership Advisory Team at the University of
16 Southern Maine to increase the contract by $20,000 to evaluate mentoring program options
17 for youth who have extended care and support agreements with the department pursuant to
18 the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, section 4037-A. The Youth Leadership Advisory
19 Team shall research mentoring programs that are evidence-based to recommend a
20 mentoring program model to the department. The mentoring program must include training
21 requirements for supporting youth transitioning out of extended care and support
22 agreements for mentors, staff and youth, as well as multiple data collection points and data
23 analysis. The Youth Leadership Advisory Team shall consult with youth who currently
24 have extended care and support agreements or have had extended care and support
25 agreements in the past. The amendment to the contract must allow for compensation,
26 including supplies and travel, for youth who are involved in the development of the
27 mentoring program. The department shall submit a report to the joint standing committee
28 of the Legislature having jurisdiction over health and human services matters, no later than
29 January 2, 2027, with recommendations for a mentoring program. The report must include
30 the recommendations from the Youth Leadership Advisory Team, descriptions of youth
31 viewpoints and the department's response to the recommendations. The joint standing
32 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over health and human services matters is
33 authorized to report out legislation related to the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.
34 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
35 appropriations and allocations are made.
36 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
